            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "St. Mira’s Secondary School is where I was brought up. A school of not only knowledge but also taught us caring, sharing & service. Its a girls school.\n\nThe motive of our school is to give give and give.\n\nThe school not only teaches academics but also encourages girls in sports, computers, stitching, painting, dancing and many such other activities. Girls who pass out from this school are all rounders and multi talented. They are highly skilled and can live on their own their future life. Girls from St. Mira’s will never be dependent on anyone in any manner.\n\nThe school teachers are remarkable and have set a bench mark.\n\nMany girls of St. Mira’s have been on the highest peak of their life to name some are:-\n1. Annapurna Bothate who is Lt. Colonel\n2. Soneya Newaskar who is also in the Army at great ranks.\n3. Nupur Nandrekar and Myself Ashwini Padavkar we are National Handball players.",
